WEBVTT

00:47.813 --> 00:50.716
[upbeat music]

01:13.572 --> 01:16.576
[upbeat music continues]

01:21.147 --> 01:24.150
[indistinct chatter]

01:26.685 --> 01:28.851
[Ivan] <i>An accomplished
bank robber and escape artist,</i>

01:28.853 --> 01:30.119
<i>Willie Sutton,</i>

01:30.121 --> 01:33.689
<i>was once asked by a reporter
why he robbed banks.</i>

01:33.691 --> 01:35.192
<i>Sutton remarked,</i>

01:35.194 --> 01:36.463
<i>"Because that's
where the money is."</i>

01:37.563 --> 01:40.567
[indistinct chatter]

01:43.234 --> 01:45.401
Hey, asshole!

01:45.403 --> 01:47.303
[Ivan] <i>And Sutton was right.</i>

01:47.305 --> 01:48.871
<i>Money is in the bank.</i>

01:48.873 --> 01:50.773
<i>But it's also in the wallets,</i>

01:50.775 --> 01:53.544
<i>the shoeboxes, cookie jars,</i>

01:53.546 --> 01:55.648
<i>and the private homes
of the unencumbered.</i>

01:57.715 --> 01:59.718
[overlapping dialogue]

02:02.587 --> 02:04.555
[Ivan]
<i>If Sutton were alive today,</i>

02:04.557 --> 02:06.356
<i>he wouldn't be robbing banks.</i>

02:06.358 --> 02:08.324
<i>He'd be robbing the wealthy.</i>

02:08.326 --> 02:11.563
<i>They're cavalier, entitled,
and unsuspecting.</i>

02:13.365 --> 02:15.899
<i>They'll hang a couple
of million dollars on the wall,</i>

02:15.901 --> 02:18.501
<i>and invite everyone over
to get drunk.</i>

02:18.503 --> 02:20.906
[machine beeping]

02:24.376 --> 02:25.378
[clicks]

02:27.780 --> 02:30.783
[ominous music]

02:47.599 --> 02:49.468
[bottle clatters]

02:54.272 --> 02:56.276
[foreboding music]

02:59.510 --> 03:01.811
[indistinct chatter]

03:01.813 --> 03:03.380
[food sizzling]

03:03.382 --> 03:05.482
- [man] Potatoes with that?
- [woman] No.

03:05.484 --> 03:07.353
[indistinct chatter]

03:10.355 --> 03:13.592
[overlapping dialogue]

03:18.764 --> 03:19.829
Hey.

03:19.831 --> 03:21.430
Hello.

03:21.432 --> 03:23.767
Can I, uh, put this somewhere?

03:23.769 --> 03:25.471
- Thrown it on the pile.
- Thanks.

03:27.573 --> 03:31.308
Hey, uh, do you know
where the fellas are?

03:31.310 --> 03:33.876
- By the piano.
- Oh. There they are.

03:33.878 --> 03:35.445
Hey, man.
Can I, uh, get one of those?

03:35.447 --> 03:36.649
Take this one.

03:37.415 --> 03:38.281
[Ivan] Cheers.

03:38.283 --> 03:40.816
- [woman 1] I understand.
- [woman 2] Yeah.

03:40.818 --> 03:44.054
[indistinct chatter]

03:44.056 --> 03:45.621
[man 1] My grandson
likes this, too.

03:45.623 --> 03:48.324
I'm teaching my grandson
magic now.

03:48.326 --> 03:50.994
- My wife calls it child abuse.
- [guests chattering]

03:50.996 --> 03:52.328
Take two fingers.

03:52.330 --> 03:54.930
Like that. Give it a little tug.

03:54.932 --> 03:57.500
Good job.
You loosened it up for me.

03:57.502 --> 03:58.734
[smacks lips]

03:58.736 --> 04:00.703
Now, I'll take this knot.

04:00.705 --> 04:03.639
I want you to place it
in that young gentleman's hand,

04:03.641 --> 04:05.811
and introduce yourselves.
That's you, son.

04:06.512 --> 04:07.778
Uh...

04:07.780 --> 04:10.383
- Hi. I'm Marguerite.
- I'm Russell.

04:11.349 --> 04:13.019
Do that here. Take that.

04:14.353 --> 04:15.786
Next, uh, left hand up, okay?

04:15.788 --> 04:18.387
And then the knot goes
in that hand, right there.

04:18.389 --> 04:19.755
- [Ivan] Over the top, right?
- [man 1] Oh, look at you.

04:19.757 --> 04:21.925
You're perfect. Watch this.

04:21.927 --> 04:24.327
[snaps]
[man 1] Open your hand.

04:24.329 --> 04:25.529
[man 1 laughs]
I love this part.

04:25.531 --> 04:26.997
I'll take those.
[chuckles]

04:26.999 --> 04:28.699
You're killing me.
Here, you take those.

04:28.701 --> 04:29.765
[whispers]
Thank you.

04:29.767 --> 04:30.901
Is that your real name?

04:30.903 --> 04:32.069
Yeah, of course.

04:32.071 --> 04:33.637
- Really?
- No.

04:33.639 --> 04:34.641
[Marguerite chuckles]

04:35.607 --> 04:37.841
So, what brings you here
tonight?

04:37.843 --> 04:40.043
Uh, you know,
I just love poetry.

04:40.045 --> 04:42.478
- What about you?
- Oh.

04:42.480 --> 04:44.413
Yeah. It's my absolute
favorite thing ever.

04:44.415 --> 04:45.981
Oh, yeah? What kinds?

04:45.983 --> 04:48.485
I mean, epic, self-conscious,

04:48.487 --> 04:49.853
limerick, haiku, free verse.

04:49.855 --> 04:50.921
Slam?

04:50.923 --> 04:53.423
That is the form at its finest.

04:53.425 --> 04:54.824
Sure.

04:54.826 --> 04:57.560
No, seriously, what are you...
What are you doing here?

04:57.562 --> 05:00.430
I'm, uh...
I'm an art consultant.

05:00.432 --> 05:01.964
What the fuck does that mean?

05:01.966 --> 05:04.067
[glass clinks]

05:04.069 --> 05:05.969
Holy shit.
I can't believe that works.

05:05.971 --> 05:07.671
- [all laugh]
- Ahh...

05:07.673 --> 05:09.772
I'm a bit more shit-faced
than planned.

05:09.774 --> 05:11.041
[Michael] Surprise, surprise!

05:11.043 --> 05:13.409
All right.
Fuck you very much, Michael.

05:13.411 --> 05:14.478
Uh, as we all know,

05:14.480 --> 05:17.514
Michael here has
a new book of poems.

05:17.516 --> 05:19.382
- [man 2] Yes.
- [crowd cheers]

05:19.384 --> 05:22.618
[Ian] A light smattering
of applause for poetry.

05:22.620 --> 05:23.586
Wonderful.

05:23.588 --> 05:26.723
Everybody, if you wanna grab
your beverages,

05:26.725 --> 05:28.024
and follow me out
to the pool house

05:28.026 --> 05:31.161
where we can entice Michael
to read some poems.

05:31.163 --> 05:32.928
- [Michael muttering]
- [man 2] Please.

05:32.930 --> 05:34.430
Hold it. Hold it a minute.

05:34.432 --> 05:35.832
- [applause]
- One. One poem.

05:35.834 --> 05:37.099
[Ian] Two poems from Michael.

05:37.101 --> 05:40.670
[Michael] "One." I said, "One."
You heard me say "one," right?

05:40.672 --> 05:42.505
I'm gonna get another,
uh, glass of red wine.

05:42.507 --> 05:44.440
- Do you want something?
- Sure. What the hell?

05:44.442 --> 05:45.444
I'll be outside.

05:46.879 --> 05:48.881
[indistinct chatter]

05:57.122 --> 05:59.992
[foreboding music]

06:06.831 --> 06:09.999
[gloves snapping]

06:17.742 --> 06:20.043
All right. As negotiated,

06:20.045 --> 06:22.178
I am going to read one poem.

06:22.180 --> 06:23.980
I think he means two.

06:23.982 --> 06:25.514
All right. I'll read two

06:25.516 --> 06:26.916
if someone shuts
this asshole up.

06:26.918 --> 06:27.919
[all laugh]

06:29.987 --> 06:31.591
[clinks]

06:32.490 --> 06:34.426
[air hissing]

06:44.702 --> 06:45.704
[grunts]

06:46.939 --> 06:47.939
[groans]

06:52.877 --> 06:53.879
[rattling]

07:00.052 --> 07:01.052
[groans]

07:05.757 --> 07:06.759
[exhales]

07:08.560 --> 07:10.028
[girl] Put your hands up!

07:11.562 --> 07:12.564
[Ivan] Uh-oh!

07:13.732 --> 07:14.734
You got me.

07:16.067 --> 07:17.767
- Bang.
- Oh!

07:17.769 --> 07:19.702
That was close.

07:19.704 --> 07:20.971
[girl] What are you doing?

07:20.973 --> 07:22.137
Uh... It's a rug.

07:22.139 --> 07:23.507
Someone spilled some wine on it,

07:23.509 --> 07:25.140
so I'm gonna take it
to the cleaners.

07:25.142 --> 07:26.445
Where are my dads?

07:26.978 --> 07:28.611
Your dads are...

07:28.613 --> 07:30.813
Your dads are at the pool house.
Over there.

07:30.815 --> 07:32.214
You wanna go...
You wanna go and see them?

07:32.216 --> 07:33.884
- [girl] Yes.
- Okay.

07:33.886 --> 07:35.985
How old are you?
I bet you're six, right?

07:35.987 --> 07:37.988
- [girl] I'm four.
- You're four?

07:37.990 --> 07:40.789
Wow! Now that is advanced.

07:40.791 --> 07:42.091
Let's go see 'em.

07:42.093 --> 07:43.161
[Ivan] Hey, uh...

07:43.995 --> 07:45.695
Could you do me a favor?

07:45.697 --> 07:47.699
- [girl] Okay.
- Great. Let's go.

07:49.567 --> 07:51.166
[Michael] "What is this labor?"

07:51.168 --> 07:53.637
That guy told me
to bring you this.

07:53.639 --> 07:54.704
[Marguerite] Which guy?

07:54.706 --> 07:55.775
That guy.

07:57.543 --> 07:58.774
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

07:58.776 --> 08:00.142
[Michael] For the life...

08:00.144 --> 08:01.211
to peel.

08:01.213 --> 08:02.711
- [man 3] What's in the bag?
- Huh.

08:02.713 --> 08:03.947
[Ivan] You mean,
"Who's in the bag?" Right?

08:03.949 --> 08:04.951
[Ivan chuckles]

08:06.218 --> 08:10.122
- [indistinct chatter]
- [car alarms blaring]

08:11.822 --> 08:13.856
[man 4] I need the key
for the one on the right.

08:13.858 --> 08:15.724
- [woman 3] I got it!
- [man 4] Thanks.

08:15.726 --> 08:16.825
[woman 3] No problem.

08:16.827 --> 08:18.830
[car alarms blaring]

08:26.572 --> 08:27.572
[keys jangling]

08:30.242 --> 08:32.945
[machine whirring]

08:36.881 --> 08:39.885
[rattling]

08:48.826 --> 08:50.830
[suspenseful music]

09:11.649 --> 09:12.784
[man whistles]

09:14.686 --> 09:15.687
[rattles]

09:31.736 --> 09:32.904
[man whistles]

09:37.643 --> 09:39.979
[suspenseful music]

09:46.350 --> 09:47.352
[alarm beeps]

09:48.220 --> 09:49.221
[clicks]

10:01.899 --> 10:03.668
[clanks, clicks]

10:04.336 --> 10:06.869
[beeping]

10:06.871 --> 10:08.838
[siren blaring in distance]

10:08.840 --> 10:10.242
[phone ringing]

10:15.346 --> 10:17.147
Thank you for making it
so quickly.

10:17.149 --> 10:19.416
Uh, I'm gonna just
get down to it.

10:19.418 --> 10:21.017
- [Ivan] Sure.
- It's come to a point

10:21.019 --> 10:23.386
where we can't really
keep up with him.

10:23.388 --> 10:25.088
[Ivan] Right. Understood.

10:25.090 --> 10:26.890
Yeah. We have to take
into consideration

10:26.892 --> 10:28.791
the community at large.
We're a small group.

10:28.793 --> 10:30.826
And, frankly, as much as we love

10:30.828 --> 10:33.195
having Raymond around,
he's just...

10:33.197 --> 10:35.464
a lot for us to handle,
as I'm...

10:35.466 --> 10:37.700
- sure you're aware.
- Yeah. No.

10:37.702 --> 10:39.703
No, no, of course. Um...

10:39.705 --> 10:42.305
Can you give me an indication
of, of his behavior,

10:42.307 --> 10:43.239
what he's doing?

10:43.241 --> 10:45.874
Yes, but, uh...
First, here are his papers

10:45.876 --> 10:47.276
and some of his drawings.

10:47.278 --> 10:49.215
I think he has everything else
with him.

10:50.481 --> 10:51.750
Ah...

10:53.719 --> 10:54.787
[Ivan chuckles]

10:56.922 --> 10:57.956
Excellent.

11:00.392 --> 11:02.157
It's the prostitutes.

11:02.159 --> 11:03.059
I'm sorry?

11:03.061 --> 11:05.228
Well, he's bribing
the security guards,

11:05.230 --> 11:07.830
stockpiling lithium,
Adderall, and Xylo-Pfan,

11:07.832 --> 11:11.100
and trading that to prostitutes
who give him barbiturates.

11:11.102 --> 11:13.469
Yeah. They're...
They're prostitutes?

11:13.471 --> 11:16.406
We're a municipal volunteer
halfway house.

11:16.408 --> 11:18.340
We do what we can, but...

11:18.342 --> 11:19.743
we're in the middle of the city.

11:19.745 --> 11:21.210
Yeah, of course.

11:21.212 --> 11:22.845
[Mary] I'm really sorry.

11:22.847 --> 11:24.280
He's a lovely guy
to have around,

11:24.282 --> 11:26.916
but with these fragile people,
it's just...

11:26.918 --> 11:29.084
- It's too dangerous.
- [Ivan] Mm-hm.

11:29.086 --> 11:31.256
[Mary] <i>I have a feeling
your brother will be just fine.</i>

11:32.758 --> 11:33.926
[Ray sighs]

11:35.527 --> 11:37.227
You wanna hear a joke?

11:37.229 --> 11:38.230
Why the fuck not?

11:39.431 --> 11:40.432
Okay.

11:42.100 --> 11:44.269
An Irishman walks out of a bar.

11:49.807 --> 11:51.373
- [both chuckle]
- That's awful.

11:51.375 --> 11:53.142
- [door opens]
- [inhales deeply]

11:53.144 --> 11:54.312
[exhales]

11:55.980 --> 11:57.379
This is my stop.

11:57.381 --> 11:58.982
[Ray groans]

11:58.984 --> 12:00.116
[Mick] All right, man.
You take care.

12:00.118 --> 12:01.785
[Ray] Yep. You too.

12:01.787 --> 12:02.788
Hey.

12:05.856 --> 12:07.860
[tense music]

12:12.330 --> 12:13.863
[Ivan] Do you wanna
eat something?

12:13.865 --> 12:14.866
[Ray] Yeah.

12:16.067 --> 12:17.533
[Ivan] You heard about Dad?

12:17.535 --> 12:18.737
[Ray] Yeah.

12:24.809 --> 12:26.211
We should probably
have a funeral.

12:27.578 --> 12:28.780
[door chimes]

12:29.413 --> 12:30.448
It sucks.

12:33.184 --> 12:34.883
Well, how about, um...

12:34.885 --> 12:36.886
a moment of silence?

12:36.888 --> 12:38.423
- Sure. Mm-hm.
- Sound nice?

12:40.057 --> 12:41.059
[silverware clinks]

12:55.273 --> 12:57.507
How many more moments
do you wanna do?

12:57.509 --> 12:59.342
[scoffs]
What's the matter with you, man?

12:59.344 --> 13:00.443
Nothing. You just had a moment.

13:00.445 --> 13:02.177
That was a moment
of silence here.

13:02.179 --> 13:03.478
I'm trying to say goodbye
to my father.

13:03.480 --> 13:05.214
Okay.

13:05.216 --> 13:06.449
Is something going on with you?

13:06.451 --> 13:07.983
- No.
- You mad at me?

13:07.985 --> 13:08.884
- No.
- You worried about me?

13:08.886 --> 13:09.920
You don't have to be worried
about me.

13:09.922 --> 13:10.987
- I'm not worried.
- I can take care of myself,

13:10.989 --> 13:13.156
- or we're doomed.
- I... I'm not worried about you.

13:13.158 --> 13:14.390
You know what?
I'm gonna do something for you.

13:14.392 --> 13:16.025
- Yeah. What?
- I want you to listen to me.

13:16.027 --> 13:17.459
- [pills rattling]
- All right?

13:17.461 --> 13:20.032
- Oh, god!
- Just hear me out on this stuff.

13:21.399 --> 13:22.835
Oh. All right.

13:23.368 --> 13:25.368
Diazepam. Right?

13:25.370 --> 13:26.969
Any of the benzos.

13:26.971 --> 13:28.470
[Ivan] Mm-hm.

13:28.472 --> 13:29.372
These are very helpful
if you need

13:29.374 --> 13:31.476
just a little bit of relief.
All right?

13:33.177 --> 13:34.509
So...

13:34.511 --> 13:38.882
All right. Then you got
your dextroamphetamines.

13:38.884 --> 13:41.217
Now, this is the stuff they gave
the super soldiers in Vietnam.

13:41.219 --> 13:44.387
All right? This is a very
practical, 48-hour solution

13:44.389 --> 13:45.921
for the situations that,
you know,

13:45.923 --> 13:47.556
require a little bit
more attention.

13:47.558 --> 13:49.093
- Okay?
- Sounds perfect.

13:51.162 --> 13:52.295
- Think about it.
- Okay.

13:52.297 --> 13:53.296
- I'll think about it.
- That's... You can only, that...

13:53.298 --> 13:55.230
That, you can just get by
with just a half.

13:55.232 --> 13:56.431
I'll think about it.

13:56.433 --> 13:58.837
Did you steal the orphans'
collection can off the counter?

14:00.238 --> 14:01.407
Oh, yeah. Maybe.

14:03.475 --> 14:05.474
- Eagle eyes.
- [Ivan] Mm-hm.

14:05.476 --> 14:06.443
You want me to, uh...

14:06.445 --> 14:08.478
[Ivan] Yeah.
That'd probably be best, right?

14:08.480 --> 14:09.545
[Ray clears throat]

14:09.547 --> 14:11.079
Hi. Uh, sir,

14:11.081 --> 14:12.949
- I just, uh...
- [coins rattling]

14:12.951 --> 14:14.316
managed to, uh,

14:14.318 --> 14:18.220
apprehend the charity tin
from that, uh...

14:18.222 --> 14:22.658
corner. The table there
of the... the punk rockers.

14:22.660 --> 14:24.594
[Ray] You might wanna check
the kitty. That feels...

14:24.596 --> 14:26.228
I don't know.
A little bit light to me.

14:26.230 --> 14:27.232
[manager] Thank you, sir.

14:28.466 --> 14:29.500
Thank you, son.

14:34.172 --> 14:35.507
[sighs]

14:36.041 --> 14:37.042
[thuds]

14:38.442 --> 14:40.343
I mean, well, well, well.

14:40.345 --> 14:42.344
You gotta jiggle the handle.

14:42.346 --> 14:43.979
Excuse me! I mean...

14:43.981 --> 14:45.515
Anyway, this is you.

14:45.517 --> 14:47.950
Well, it's not much,
but it should do for now. Okay?

14:47.952 --> 14:50.386
You got a list
of the local amenities, man?

14:50.388 --> 14:52.254
Maybe a... a map of the area.

14:52.256 --> 14:54.489
My wife and I were just thinking
about taking a quick tour.

14:54.491 --> 14:56.059
[Ivan] It's temporary.
All right?

14:56.061 --> 14:58.393
We're gonna find you something
better, but, you know...

14:58.395 --> 15:00.128
[Ray] Sure.

15:00.130 --> 15:01.196
You can't stay here.

15:01.198 --> 15:02.967
I'm seeing someone, and...

15:03.999 --> 15:04.334
she comes here
from time to time.

15:04.336 --> 15:07.236
Oh, from time to time?
You're not seeing anybody.

15:07.238 --> 15:08.304
[Ivan] What?

15:08.306 --> 15:10.540
[Ray] You're not seeing anybody.

15:10.542 --> 15:12.407
- Uh, yes, I am.
- [fridge door thuds]

15:12.409 --> 15:14.310
- No, you're not.
- [chuckles]

15:14.312 --> 15:16.079
Actually, yes, I am.

15:16.081 --> 15:17.412
Actually,
you just said "actually"

15:17.414 --> 15:19.015
while closing your eyes.
That's a tell.

15:19.017 --> 15:20.717
Also, there's not tampons
or extra toothbrush

15:20.719 --> 15:22.719
in the bathroom.
You know what, I think...

15:22.721 --> 15:23.719
I'm gonna go.
I'm gonna get out of here.

15:23.721 --> 15:25.421
[Ivan] No, no, don't do that.
Don't do that.

15:25.423 --> 15:27.323
- Don't do that, Ray.
- Hey, I'm kidding.

15:27.325 --> 15:29.224
Where else am I gonna go?

15:29.226 --> 15:32.130
Look, I'm, I'm grateful
for even one night here.

15:33.063 --> 15:34.065
Thank you.

15:36.634 --> 15:38.070
Put it in the vise.

15:39.269 --> 15:41.403
- Uh...
- Put it in the vise.

15:41.405 --> 15:43.071
[chuckles]
Okay. Good.

15:43.073 --> 15:44.140
Come here.

15:44.142 --> 15:45.144
[Ray groans]

15:46.677 --> 15:48.578
Okay. Okay. We're good, man.

15:48.580 --> 15:50.950
- Yeah.
- [Ivan] Okay. Okeydokey.

15:51.716 --> 15:53.016
Okay. That's enough.

15:53.018 --> 15:54.086
All right. Yeah.

15:57.322 --> 15:58.688
No prostitutes.

15:58.690 --> 15:59.692
I like that.

16:01.426 --> 16:03.429
[slow sensual music]

16:05.230 --> 16:06.628
[Dimitri groans]

16:06.630 --> 16:07.665
[giggles]

16:08.566 --> 16:12.571
[phone ringing, buzzing]

16:17.075 --> 16:19.374
- [moaning]
- All right, that's it.

16:19.376 --> 16:21.012
We gotta wrap it up for today.
That's it.

16:27.519 --> 16:28.519
[creaks]

16:31.755 --> 16:34.357
[clanking]

16:34.359 --> 16:37.096
[wheels rattling]

16:39.163 --> 16:40.765
[engines whirring]

16:43.368 --> 16:44.370
[horse snorts]

16:47.172 --> 16:48.704
[horse whinnies]

16:48.706 --> 16:50.709
[tense music]

17:03.421 --> 17:04.487
[concierge] Can I help you?

17:04.489 --> 17:06.321
Yeah. Uh, I'm meeting someone.

17:06.324 --> 17:07.556
Do you have a reservation?

17:07.558 --> 17:09.459
Hmm... Namath.

17:09.461 --> 17:10.693
[concierge] <i>Oh, it looks like
you're the first to arrive.</i>

17:10.694 --> 17:13.263
<i>You can have a seat at the bar,
and I'll get you set up.</i>

17:15.799 --> 17:17.269
- [Dimitri] <i>Ivan.</i>
- [Ivan] <i>Mm.</i>

17:17.769 --> 17:18.867
[smooches]

17:18.868 --> 17:20.335
Glass of red wine.

17:20.337 --> 17:21.770
[bartender] Any particular type?

17:21.771 --> 17:23.238
Yeah, in a glass.

17:23.240 --> 17:24.806
Red. Down there.

17:24.808 --> 17:26.412
- [bartender] Got it.
- Thanks.

17:26.877 --> 17:28.210
[Dimitri] Come.

17:28.212 --> 17:30.345
So, uh, you got the money, yeah?

17:30.347 --> 17:32.715
Yeah. I gave it
to one of your guys.

17:32.717 --> 17:34.749
Great.

17:34.751 --> 17:37.056
So, what are we, uh...
What are we doing here?

17:38.155 --> 17:39.689
[Ivan] I wanted to talk.

17:39.691 --> 17:40.726
Oh, yeah?

17:41.759 --> 17:43.062
About, uh...

17:44.295 --> 17:46.129
About what exactly?

17:46.131 --> 17:47.499
Well, uh...

17:49.334 --> 17:50.602
by my count, we're close.

17:51.402 --> 17:52.668
Yeah, we're close.

17:52.670 --> 17:55.203
Absolutely. I mean, I have to
check a little more carefully.

17:55.205 --> 17:57.208
Your father was into me
for quite a bit.

17:59.743 --> 18:01.710
He used to sit right up there
at that bar, your old man,

18:01.712 --> 18:03.478
every day with his rice pudding

18:03.480 --> 18:04.782
and the <i>Daily Racing Form.</i>

18:05.849 --> 18:07.251
Never missed a day.

18:08.318 --> 18:09.785
You never got the bug for that?

18:09.787 --> 18:11.254
It's not for me, but look.

18:11.256 --> 18:12.822
Uh, I think I have two more.

18:12.824 --> 18:15.391
Two more, then I'm done.
Then I'm out.

18:15.393 --> 18:17.459
You might take it easy. I'll
take your word for it, okay?

18:17.461 --> 18:18.561
- [Dimitri] Take it easy.
- We talked about this.

18:18.563 --> 18:20.496
No, no. You talked about this.

18:20.498 --> 18:23.231
You talked about it, Ivan.

18:23.233 --> 18:26.401
So, your little shoebox
is full now? That's adorable.

18:26.403 --> 18:27.702
Let me explain something to you

18:27.704 --> 18:29.337
that your father
explained to me.

18:29.339 --> 18:30.573
You have to make hay

18:30.575 --> 18:32.408
while the sun shines.

18:32.410 --> 18:33.875
[Dimitri] You understand
what that means?

18:33.877 --> 18:36.478
Yeah. How'd that work out
for him?

18:36.480 --> 18:38.948
It's a game of discipline.

18:38.950 --> 18:41.950
There are certain forms
that have to be observed.

18:41.952 --> 18:43.321
Of course, you get that.

18:44.721 --> 18:45.723
[Dimitri] Hmm.

18:47.458 --> 18:48.857
One little heart attack
years ago,

18:48.859 --> 18:50.426
I have to take
these fucking horse pills

18:50.428 --> 18:51.760
the whole rest of my life.

18:51.762 --> 18:53.365
- [phone buzzing]
- Excuse me.

18:54.332 --> 18:55.601
[buzzing continues]

18:57.335 --> 18:58.336
[Dimitri] Oh.

18:59.604 --> 19:00.605
[clicks]

19:01.573 --> 19:03.206
You look like shit.

19:03.208 --> 19:05.144
No, I'm okay.
I'm just not sleeping.

19:06.310 --> 19:07.709
[Dimitri] Stop smoking.

19:07.711 --> 19:08.944
Best thing I ever did.

19:08.946 --> 19:11.613
Yeah, I tried that.
I quit two years ago.

19:11.615 --> 19:13.915
So, start smoking.
Fuck do I know?

19:13.917 --> 19:16.686
Look, I got a busy day
ahead of me, okay?

19:16.688 --> 19:17.786
I promise you,

19:17.788 --> 19:20.722
I'm gonna check into
your dad's ticket, all right?

19:20.724 --> 19:23.392
There's something you need
to understand, Ivan.

19:23.394 --> 19:24.492
I trust you.

19:24.494 --> 19:27.263
That's what this is based on.
I love you. I mean,

19:27.265 --> 19:28.631
you're like a son to me.

19:28.633 --> 19:31.467
That's why it's so important
to me that you succeed.

19:31.469 --> 19:32.901
Yeah, and I, and I get that,

19:32.903 --> 19:34.870
and I appreciate everything
you've done for me,

19:34.872 --> 19:37.373
but I'm not gonna do
this forever. I need a number.

19:37.375 --> 19:38.807
You're gonna get
a fucking number, okay.

19:38.809 --> 19:40.508
Keep your pants on, all right?

19:40.510 --> 19:42.277
It's rather complicated.

19:42.279 --> 19:43.645
There's things involved
you don't understand.

19:43.647 --> 19:45.750
I have to work in your
father's vig, all right?

19:47.751 --> 19:49.421
All right? Off you go.

19:50.320 --> 19:51.689
[inhales sharply]

19:52.490 --> 19:53.756
[sighs]

19:53.758 --> 19:55.760
[foreboding music]

19:59.263 --> 20:00.264
[sighs]

20:00.832 --> 20:01.833
What?

20:04.736 --> 20:05.737
Nothing.

20:09.406 --> 20:11.409
[tense music]

20:13.845 --> 20:15.614
[slurping]

20:23.654 --> 20:24.754
[concierge] Hi.

20:24.756 --> 20:25.689
- [man 5] How you doing?
- [concierge] Can I help you?

20:25.691 --> 20:26.590
[man 5] Just meeting
a friend for lunch.

20:26.592 --> 20:28.457
[concierge]
Name for the reservation?

20:28.459 --> 20:29.624
Namath.

20:29.626 --> 20:31.294
[concierge] Okay.

20:31.296 --> 20:32.795
- Can I help you with that?
- No.

20:32.797 --> 20:33.863
Thank you.

20:33.865 --> 20:34.865
[concierge] Follow me.

20:39.336 --> 20:40.568
[water trickling]

20:40.570 --> 20:41.937
[curtain rattles]

20:41.939 --> 20:43.976
[upbeat music]

20:45.509 --> 20:46.778
[machine whirring]

20:55.586 --> 20:56.587
[rattles]

21:14.338 --> 21:16.340
[upbeat music continues]

21:26.550 --> 21:28.017
[engine starts]

21:28.019 --> 21:31.722
[lively music plays via stereo]

21:35.359 --> 21:36.827
- [door opens]
- [lively music stops]

21:39.364 --> 21:40.462
[thuds]

21:40.464 --> 21:42.398
[man 6] Yeah, last week,
it was a little bit nuts...

21:42.400 --> 21:43.498
[valet]
I'll back that up for you.

21:43.500 --> 21:44.600
[overlapping dialogue]

21:44.602 --> 21:45.801
[valet] Last spot on the left.

21:45.803 --> 21:46.901
[Ivan] Hey, man.

21:46.903 --> 21:48.571
I just dropped someone off.
Can I use your bathroom?

21:48.573 --> 21:49.872
The bathroom for the help
is over here.

21:49.874 --> 21:50.909
- Great, thanks.
- [keys jangle]

21:52.943 --> 21:54.945
[tense music]

21:59.450 --> 22:02.117
[breathes deeply]

22:02.119 --> 22:03.321
[clanks]

22:04.588 --> 22:05.656
[doorknob clinks]

22:06.790 --> 22:07.856
Whoa!

22:07.858 --> 22:08.960
Whoa!
[chuckles]

22:09.926 --> 22:11.093
[Ivan exhales]

22:11.095 --> 22:12.428
You're following me.

22:12.430 --> 22:13.328
Yeah, of course.

22:13.330 --> 22:15.430
You've, uh, changed
something though.

22:15.432 --> 22:16.931
Can't figure it out.

22:16.933 --> 22:17.999
What are you doing here?

22:18.001 --> 22:20.536
Uh, it is a big,
big charity event.

22:20.538 --> 22:22.938
[scoffs]
What charity is that?

22:22.940 --> 22:24.739
Oh, it's the one, you know,

22:24.741 --> 22:26.674
everyone's talking about.
It's uh...

22:26.676 --> 22:28.878
They're helping out with
all sorts of stuff. You know?

22:28.880 --> 22:30.078
Kids...
[clears throat]

22:30.080 --> 22:32.148
...water, literacy,

22:32.150 --> 22:34.549
- dolphins.
- [Marguerite] Mmm. Dolphins.

22:34.551 --> 22:35.418
Yeah. No, I...

22:35.420 --> 22:37.723
- I love that charity. Of course.
- Right.

22:39.690 --> 22:42.490
I, um, actually have a favor
to ask you,

22:42.492 --> 22:43.558
but I have to pee, so...

22:43.560 --> 22:44.596
- just wait.
- Mm-hm.

22:45.797 --> 22:46.929
[Ivan exhales]

22:46.931 --> 22:48.533
[Marguerite]
Can you hear me peeing?

22:48.965 --> 22:50.032
Yep.

22:50.034 --> 22:52.133
Mm. Gross. Get farther away.

22:52.135 --> 22:53.137
[Ivan] Hm.

22:58.442 --> 23:00.612
[water trickling]

23:02.980 --> 23:05.213
- Thanks.
- Sure.

23:05.215 --> 23:08.049
So, um, I came here,
obviously, for charity.

23:08.051 --> 23:09.951
- Obviously.
- Thank you.

23:09.953 --> 23:12.220
And, um, because this, uh,

23:12.222 --> 23:15.724
Italian producer guy is making
this thing I want a part in.

23:15.726 --> 23:17.860
But, um, he's just sort of
hitting on me.

23:17.862 --> 23:18.861
- Oh!
- Yeah.

23:18.863 --> 23:21.729
So I, I told him that
my boyfriend was coming.

23:21.731 --> 23:22.797
[Ivan] Okay.

23:22.799 --> 23:24.834
What's the part?

23:24.836 --> 23:27.001
It's, um, too embarrassing
to talk about.

23:27.003 --> 23:28.837
Come on. It's gonna be
a lot easier for me

23:28.839 --> 23:29.904
to be your fake boyfriend

23:29.906 --> 23:31.774
if I knew something
about the part.

23:31.776 --> 23:34.809
Okay. Well, it's an Italian
horror film,

23:34.811 --> 23:37.580
- and I play a witch bride.
- [gasps]

23:37.582 --> 23:38.547
- Doesn't sound so bad.
- [Marguerite sighs]

23:38.549 --> 23:40.482
I'm naked for three-fourths
of the movie.

23:40.484 --> 23:41.584
Ah! A genre picture.

23:41.586 --> 23:42.852
[Marguerite] Mm-hm.

23:42.854 --> 23:43.986
Will you, um...

23:43.988 --> 23:46.788
be my fake boyfriend or not?

23:46.790 --> 23:48.923
- Sure.
- [glasses clink]

23:48.925 --> 23:50.492
[Ivan] Let's see
if we can spot him, eh?

23:50.494 --> 23:51.596
- Okay.
- [Ivan] Hm.

23:52.797 --> 23:54.896
[Ivan sucking teeth]

23:54.898 --> 23:56.265
Is, uh...

23:56.267 --> 23:57.999
that him, six o'clock?

23:58.001 --> 23:59.834
[indistinct chatter]

23:59.836 --> 24:01.636
- How'd you do that?
- I don't know.

24:01.638 --> 24:02.671
Just seems like him.

24:02.673 --> 24:05.039
Yeah, but there are a lot
of candidates here.

24:05.041 --> 24:07.042
Only three Italian ones.

24:07.044 --> 24:08.576
That guy, and he's not a creep.

24:08.578 --> 24:09.812
- He's almost dead.
- [Marguerite chuckles]

24:09.814 --> 24:12.851
And that guy through there,
and that seems pretty obvious.

24:14.652 --> 24:16.251
What about that guy?

24:16.253 --> 24:19.153
- [Ivan] That guy's Jewish.
- How do you know that?

24:19.155 --> 24:21.289
Okay. That's very impressive.

24:21.291 --> 24:22.624
- Bingo!
- Hmm.

24:22.626 --> 24:23.758
Here comes your boy.

24:23.760 --> 24:24.994
Okay. He thinks
I'm half-Italian.

24:24.996 --> 24:26.795
- You speak Italian?
- Sure. Not really.

24:26.797 --> 24:28.663
- Ah, Giovanni!
- Bella!

24:28.665 --> 24:30.266
- <i>Tutto bene, Giovanni.</i>
- [smooches]

24:30.268 --> 24:32.767
- <i>Bellissimo.</i>
- <i>Buonosera. Ivan.</i>

24:32.769 --> 24:35.703
- <i>Ah, parli Italiano?</i>
- <i>Un pochissimo.</i>

24:35.705 --> 24:37.072
- Ah!
- Is that right?

24:37.074 --> 24:38.707
[speaking Italian]

24:38.709 --> 24:39.842
[both laugh]

24:39.844 --> 24:41.544
Ah, Giovanni
and I were talking earlier

24:41.546 --> 24:43.112
about how beautiful
Paul's house is.

24:43.114 --> 24:44.747
It is gorgeous. Yeah.

24:44.749 --> 24:45.881
Very beautiful.

24:45.883 --> 24:49.552
Uh, how come you, uh, know Paul?

24:49.554 --> 24:51.152
I know Paul
through Marguerite who...

24:51.154 --> 24:53.889
- Uh, Elyse. Through me. Elyse.
- Ah.

24:53.891 --> 24:56.324
Uh, and I introduced you to Paul
at a party in New York.

24:56.326 --> 24:57.959
- Yeah, that party in New York.
- Yeah.

24:57.961 --> 24:59.128
- Mm-hm.
- I remember it very well, yes.

24:59.130 --> 25:00.595
- Mm-hm.
- Oh, Paul. Lovely guy.

25:00.597 --> 25:01.863
- He's kind of...
- Super tall.

25:01.865 --> 25:03.097
- Really tall.
- <i>Altissimo.</i>

25:03.099 --> 25:05.199
Paul. <i>Altissimo. ì, sì.</i>

25:05.201 --> 25:06.669
Paul, <i>grande, eh?</i>

25:06.671 --> 25:07.603
- Yeah.
- Mm-hm.

25:07.605 --> 25:10.573
Yeah. Eh, so, uh,
friend of friend. Mm.

25:10.575 --> 25:11.974
- Yeah.
- <i>Sì.</i>

25:11.976 --> 25:13.011
Now, um...

25:13.844 --> 25:15.744
The artwork...

25:15.746 --> 25:17.112
- So-so.
- [both] Hm.

25:17.114 --> 25:18.783
Hm, that's a Modigliani.

25:20.284 --> 25:21.616
Ah!

25:21.618 --> 25:22.851
Is he here?

25:22.853 --> 25:24.656
Uh, I think he's dead.

25:25.957 --> 25:27.890
- Oh, good!
- [all chuckle]

25:27.892 --> 25:31.093
Um... Well, I, uh,
leave you alone, eh? Huh?

25:31.095 --> 25:32.827
[speaking Italian]

25:32.829 --> 25:34.630
<i>Salute, salute.</i>

25:34.632 --> 25:35.698
- Ciao.
- Ciao.

25:35.700 --> 25:36.798
- <i>Grazie.</i>
- My pleasure.

25:36.800 --> 25:37.865
- Thank you so much.
- Giovanni.

25:37.867 --> 25:40.001
Oh, these hands, eh?
Mine disappear.

25:40.003 --> 25:41.236
- [mumbling]
- [Ivan chuckles]

25:41.238 --> 25:43.639
- A big sailor, right?
- [Ivan chuckles]

25:43.641 --> 25:45.708
- Thank you.
- Thanks.

25:45.710 --> 25:47.746
I like the look of that room.
You want to check it out?

25:48.144 --> 25:49.146
Sure.

25:50.780 --> 25:53.815
You, uh, you want a game?

25:53.817 --> 25:55.854
- Yeah.
- How about, uh...

25:56.186 --> 25:57.288
[gulps]

25:57.989 --> 25:59.254
Hundred bucks?

25:59.256 --> 26:00.122
[clicks]

26:00.124 --> 26:02.126
- [beeps]
- [Elyse] How about a thousand?

26:03.259 --> 26:04.328
[Ivan] A thousand?

26:06.631 --> 26:07.666
[inhales deeply]

26:08.098 --> 26:09.664
Why not?

26:09.666 --> 26:11.033
You're not really good, are you?

26:11.035 --> 26:12.037
Eh.
[exhales]

26:12.836 --> 26:14.071
You're full of shit.

26:15.205 --> 26:17.206
Maybe.

26:17.208 --> 26:19.177
- Six hundred. That's all I got.
- [light tapping]

26:20.744 --> 26:22.279
Uh, can you loosen this?

26:25.750 --> 26:26.750
Sure.

26:27.884 --> 26:29.320
[zipper rasps]

26:29.920 --> 26:30.922
Thanks.

26:38.996 --> 26:40.261
Is that famous?

26:40.263 --> 26:42.264
Yeah. That's Philip Guston.

26:42.266 --> 26:43.931
Mid-'40s, I think.

26:43.933 --> 26:45.668
[Ivan] Originally,
he was an abstract painter,

26:45.670 --> 26:47.268
and then became more figurative.

26:47.270 --> 26:48.804
More political.

26:48.806 --> 26:50.005
Hated Nixon.

26:50.007 --> 26:51.739
- [thuds, clatters]
- [Elyse] Is it, um...

26:51.741 --> 26:52.940
worth anything?

26:52.942 --> 26:53.944
I don't know.

26:55.880 --> 26:57.882
So why are you making
Italian horror movies?

26:59.416 --> 27:02.918
You, um, you know
who Aton Eisenstat is?

27:02.920 --> 27:05.353
- [Ivan] I do not.
- He's a Hollywood producer.

27:05.355 --> 27:07.221
[Elyse] He's about as big
as they get.

27:07.223 --> 27:09.123
Remember how they used
to say, uh...

27:09.125 --> 27:11.125
"You'll never work
in this town again, kid"?

27:11.127 --> 27:13.228
- [Ivan] Sure.
- [clacks]

27:13.230 --> 27:16.864
Well, he says it,
and he means it.

27:16.866 --> 27:18.967
[Elyse] <i>I met him
at an award show party.</i>

27:18.969 --> 27:20.869
- [laughter]
- [Elyse] <i>He was funny.</i>

27:20.871 --> 27:22.705
<i>I had been in two
or three movies.</i>

27:22.707 --> 27:25.908
<i>And I was on some list
called "Actresses to Watch."</i>

27:25.910 --> 27:27.142
<i>I was a bit drunk, and...</i>

27:27.144 --> 27:29.814
<i>he told me we were going
to an after-party at his house.</i>

27:31.182 --> 27:33.114
<i>I was young, and I just...</i>

27:33.116 --> 27:34.415
<i>I didn't know better.</i>

27:34.417 --> 27:36.151
<i>There was no after-party.</i>

27:36.153 --> 27:38.386
[tense music]

27:38.388 --> 27:41.256
<i>I, um, I hid in the bathroom
while he banged on the door,</i>

27:41.258 --> 27:43.926
<i>and then, as soon as I heard him
on the phone,</i>

27:43.928 --> 27:44.996
<i>I bounced.</i>

27:45.962 --> 27:46.964
[chuckles]

27:50.867 --> 27:51.970
[Elyse] Side pocket.

27:53.436 --> 27:54.872
[clacking]

27:56.473 --> 27:57.708
[Ivan] Well.

27:58.275 --> 27:59.908
I think...

27:59.910 --> 28:01.211
- I just got hustled.
- [thuds]

28:02.278 --> 28:04.749
Maybe, or I, um, I got lucky.

28:05.249 --> 28:06.250
Maybe.

28:08.384 --> 28:09.421
Can you, um...

28:11.288 --> 28:12.289
Sure.

28:13.324 --> 28:14.959
[zipper rasps]

28:16.861 --> 28:18.927
- How do I look?
- [door opens]

28:18.929 --> 28:21.066
[Giovanni]
Ah, there you are, Bella.

28:21.832 --> 28:24.032
[speaking Italian]

28:24.034 --> 28:25.933
I look for you everywhere.

28:25.935 --> 28:27.271
Big house.
[chuckles]

28:28.939 --> 28:30.939
[Elyse] Thank you, sweetie.
I'll see you in there.

28:30.941 --> 28:31.942
Indeed, sweetheart.

28:32.442 --> 28:33.508
[both chuckle]

28:33.510 --> 28:35.043
You kids have a great time.

28:35.045 --> 28:37.478
I want to introduce you
to my rich friend...

28:37.480 --> 28:39.014
Ah, <i>sì. Grazie.</i>

28:39.016 --> 28:41.350
<i>Que bello.</i>

28:41.352 --> 28:42.884
- [Giovanni] Ivano.
- Hm?

28:42.886 --> 28:46.955
<i>Ah, un amico, vuoi un cocktail,</i>
vino, champagne?

28:46.957 --> 28:52.260
[speaking Italian]

28:52.262 --> 28:53.862
- Okay.
- <i>Aspettiamo.</i>

28:53.864 --> 28:55.063
Ciao.

28:55.065 --> 28:56.465
[Giovanni] Oh, Jonka!

28:56.467 --> 28:57.469
[door closes]

29:00.971 --> 29:01.972
[doorknob clicks]

29:04.107 --> 29:06.110
[suspenseful music]

29:08.511 --> 29:09.780
[clinking]

29:15.118 --> 29:16.120
[jangles]

29:18.388 --> 29:20.390
[foreboding music]

29:23.928 --> 29:25.930
[device beeping]

29:26.963 --> 29:28.296
