to burn it or something.

32:20.170 --> 32:21.702
Ah, I get it. Who owns it?

32:21.704 --> 32:23.471
[Dimitri] This guy, John Wolfe.

32:23.473 --> 32:25.609
He lives deep in the Sierras
up by Mammoth.

32:26.509 --> 32:27.642
This guy made...

32:27.644 --> 32:30.045
wheelbarrows full of money
in textiles,

32:30.047 --> 32:31.546
and then he wound up buying
half of Manhattan.

32:31.548 --> 32:33.547
He owns a very
considerable collection

32:33.549 --> 32:35.383
of Nazi war memorabilia.

32:35.385 --> 32:37.753
Now as you or may not know,

32:37.755 --> 32:40.488
Hitler fancied himself
an artist.

32:40.490 --> 32:43.257
He applied to the Institute.
He got rejected.

32:43.259 --> 32:45.026
And I think we know
the end of that story.

32:45.028 --> 32:45.961
Mm-hm.

32:45.963 --> 32:47.629
[sucks teeth]
So where does he keep it?

32:47.631 --> 32:48.764
[Dimitri] On his property.

32:48.766 --> 32:50.731
Uh-huh.
What's the security like?

32:50.733 --> 32:52.169
Well, that's the thing.

32:52.769 --> 32:53.736
What's the thing?

32:53.738 --> 32:55.703
The thing is,
there really is no security.

32:55.705 --> 32:57.671
I mean, there's no alarm,
there's no surveillance.

32:57.673 --> 32:59.306
It's just him...

32:59.308 --> 33:02.643
living alone
with these two dogs.

33:02.645 --> 33:05.613
He keeps the Nazi stuff
in this kind of a war room

33:05.615 --> 33:08.083
because he holds a lot
of media mogul shit up there.

33:08.085 --> 33:09.785
And the whole thing
would be, uh...

33:09.787 --> 33:12.687
for want of a better word,
sort of verboten, you know?

33:12.689 --> 33:14.325
- [Ivan] Oh, yeah?
- And listen.

33:15.291 --> 33:17.459
This one is big.

33:17.461 --> 33:18.794
[Dimitri] I mean, big.

33:18.796 --> 33:20.828
You bring the Hitler to me,

33:20.830 --> 33:24.001
you do one more little job,
a candy from a baby thing,

33:24.835 --> 33:26.500
and that's it.

33:26.502 --> 33:28.405
You and me are done.

33:31.674 --> 33:32.740
Actually done?

33:32.742 --> 33:35.546
Like totally
and completely done.

33:37.280 --> 33:38.548
All right. Uh...

33:39.583 --> 33:41.119
What's... What's my cut?

33:41.484 --> 33:42.586
500K.

33:43.619 --> 33:45.286
This guy is an absolute nut.

33:45.288 --> 33:47.588
He will do anything
to get this piece.

33:47.590 --> 33:51.258
$500,000. I'm in
and then I'm out. We're done.

33:51.260 --> 33:52.827
Well, there is something
you should know.

33:52.829 --> 33:54.097
[Ivan] Okay, what?

33:54.730 --> 33:56.698
Back when he was in Nam,

33:56.700 --> 33:58.432
Wolfe liked to sleep
in the nude.

33:58.434 --> 34:01.335
So, one night, Charlie rolls
a bunch of grenades

34:01.337 --> 34:03.270
into this DMZ camp...

34:03.272 --> 34:05.739
- <i>Wolfe grabs two Browning 9 mm.</i>
- [rapid gunshots]

34:05.741 --> 34:06.841
[Dimitri]
<i>He slips out of his tent.</i>

34:06.843 --> 34:10.579
- <i>He executes 11 VC personally.</i>
- [explosion]

34:10.581 --> 34:13.414
[Dimitri] <i>Thirteen bullets
in each clip. That's 26 bullets.</i>

34:13.416 --> 34:15.617
<i>Eleven dead. Two shots a piece.</i>

34:15.619 --> 34:17.786
<i>One to the chest,
one to the head.</i>

34:17.788 --> 34:19.786
<i>He only misfired four bullets.</i>

34:19.789 --> 34:23.126
<i>All in the dead of night.
Totally in the nude.</i>

34:24.161 --> 34:25.525
<i>This guy's got Purple Hearts.</i>

34:25.527 --> 34:27.362
<i>He's got Silver Stars.
Everything.</i>

34:27.364 --> 34:29.362
[Eric] <i>You love that part
about him being nude.</i>

34:29.364 --> 34:30.802
Fuck you.
It was in <i>Time magazine.</i>

34:33.503 --> 34:35.202
How's the blood pressure?

34:35.204 --> 34:37.237
How does it look?

34:37.239 --> 34:39.273
[Eric] Like you swallowed
a grenade.

34:39.275 --> 34:41.277
I haven't done any blow
in over a year.

34:44.280 --> 34:46.284
[upbeat music]

34:48.851 --> 34:50.485
[Eric] I'm proud of you.

34:50.487 --> 34:51.552
Thank you.

34:51.554 --> 34:53.655
[phone rings]

34:53.657 --> 34:55.190
Hello.

34:55.192 --> 34:56.224
[Dimitri] Yeah. I know. Later.

34:56.226 --> 34:58.159
[Ivan] Okay. I gotta
hit the head before I go.

34:58.161 --> 34:59.360
- [Dimitri] Hold on one second.
- Wait! No...

34:59.362 --> 35:01.195
That one is...

35:01.197 --> 35:02.731
- out of commission.
- No, no, it's fine.

35:02.733 --> 35:03.868
It's okay.
He could use that once.

35:05.434 --> 35:06.436
Okay.

35:08.237 --> 35:10.107
[retreating footsteps]

35:27.958 --> 35:30.260
- Jesus.
- [clinking]

35:37.367 --> 35:39.537
[ominous music]

35:45.608 --> 35:47.675
I had a little bloody nose
back in there before.

35:47.677 --> 35:48.778
Sorry about that.

35:50.280 --> 35:51.415
Yeah, I saw that.

35:52.849 --> 35:54.749
Come home and see the old man?

35:54.751 --> 35:56.851
Yeah. That's right.

35:56.853 --> 35:57.889
Long time ago.

35:58.922 --> 36:01.623
Andrew Wyeth, 1950.

36:01.625 --> 36:03.793
First job your father ever did
for me, actually.

36:05.461 --> 36:08.229
[Dimitri]
I put it up in his honor.

36:08.231 --> 36:10.565
Something tells me you think
you should own it.

36:10.567 --> 36:12.434
No, I didn't say that.

36:12.436 --> 36:13.969
You didn't have to.

36:13.971 --> 36:16.706
You've got that vindictive,
moralistic look on your face.

36:17.474 --> 36:18.543
I feel it.

36:21.744 --> 36:23.778
You know what?

36:23.780 --> 36:25.950
I'm sorry
about your father. Truly.

36:27.483 --> 36:28.550
But that's spilled milk already.

36:28.552 --> 36:30.188
No use in crying
over it now, right?

36:31.021 --> 36:32.223
[Dimitri] Eric.

36:33.556 --> 36:35.289
We really should get to work.

36:35.291 --> 36:37.295
[foreboding music]

36:39.762 --> 36:40.764
Sure.

36:43.432 --> 36:45.436
[tense music]

36:45.902 --> 36:47.471
[door opens]

36:48.405 --> 36:49.407
[door closes]

36:51.574 --> 36:53.577
[birds chirping]

36:59.548 --> 37:00.617
Michael!

37:02.885 --> 37:04.422
What the fuck?

37:08.458 --> 37:10.891
Michael, get the fuck down here
right now!

37:10.893 --> 37:12.726
[Lyman] So, this here's
the original, huh?

37:12.728 --> 37:14.729
Yes.

37:14.731 --> 37:16.865
How long before you knew
it was missing?

37:16.867 --> 37:17.868
Yesterday.

37:18.534 --> 37:19.603
I see.

37:21.304 --> 37:22.804
I'm sorry. Um...

37:22.806 --> 37:24.938
Do you think you're gonna
be able to find this?

37:24.940 --> 37:25.942
I doubt it.

37:27.510 --> 37:29.811
I mean,
it'll resurface somewhere.

37:29.813 --> 37:31.713
Gray market, usually.

37:31.715 --> 37:34.648
There's a 2% recovery rate
for high-profile pieces.

37:34.650 --> 37:37.052
Oh, well, that's encouraging.

37:37.054 --> 37:38.887
Yeah. It's basically
shaking parts

37:38.889 --> 37:41.088
outta sheets at this point.

37:41.090 --> 37:44.525
[Lyman] We'd have an easier time
finding the tooth fairy.

37:44.527 --> 37:47.494
Hey, look,
I know you spoke to the LAPD,

37:47.496 --> 37:50.065
but I'm gonna ask you
one more time.

37:50.067 --> 37:52.333
Anybody at this party
we don't know?

37:52.335 --> 37:53.834
Say, uh...

37:53.836 --> 37:57.072
caterers, valet, uh, staff?

37:57.074 --> 37:59.340
I mean, these things
are usually inside baseball.

37:59.342 --> 38:00.641
No. No, we knew everyone.

38:00.643 --> 38:02.279
It was all of our regulars.

38:03.045 --> 38:04.112
Okay.

38:04.114 --> 38:05.713
[girl] Excuse me.

38:05.715 --> 38:08.650
Who's the guy
who can fix the rug?

38:08.652 --> 38:09.751
What's that now, dear?

38:09.753 --> 38:11.720
Who's the guy who took the rug?

38:11.722 --> 38:13.924
He told me to bring a drink
to that lady.

38:14.724 --> 38:16.458
Mr. Brooks,

38:16.460 --> 38:19.463
do you suppose you could provide
me with a guest list?

38:27.971 --> 38:29.005
Thanks.

38:36.413 --> 38:38.349
[man 7] Oh!
Burning the midnight oil?

38:40.384 --> 38:42.851
- It's seven o'clock.
- Yeah. No shit it is.

38:42.853 --> 38:44.952
Kings tickets. On the glass.
And I'm late.

38:44.954 --> 38:46.054
- [drawer thuds]
- [sighs]

38:46.056 --> 38:47.090
[man 7] Suck it!

39:03.639 --> 39:05.675
[clanks]

39:08.911 --> 39:12.782
[trickling]

39:15.952 --> 39:17.822
[Lyman] Jive-ass motherfucker.

39:23.626 --> 39:25.628
[suspenseful music]

39:29.800 --> 39:31.602
