47:35.518 --> 47:38.322
someone who wants to buy a house
in Costa Mesa, I guess.

47:40.456 --> 47:42.593
That's helpful. Good game.

47:44.594 --> 47:45.896
I'll see you then.

47:47.597 --> 47:48.599
[Ivan] Mm-hm.

47:51.567 --> 47:52.633
Bye.

47:52.635 --> 47:54.702
[door opens]

47:54.704 --> 47:56.440
- I'm just gonna hang here.
- [door closes]

47:57.139 --> 47:58.174
You know,

47:59.509 --> 48:00.510
chill.

48:04.380 --> 48:06.383
[foreboding music]

48:10.119 --> 48:11.989
[car engine starts]

48:26.402 --> 48:27.670
[car engine starts]

48:41.117 --> 48:43.019
[whirring]

48:44.086 --> 48:45.588
[clicking]

48:49.559 --> 48:50.994
[clicking continues]

48:54.396 --> 48:57.333
[Ray breathes deeply]

48:58.601 --> 49:00.137
You wanna hear a funny story?

49:04.639 --> 49:06.009
Have a peek at that.

49:08.643 --> 49:10.311
What is this?

49:10.313 --> 49:12.380
[Ray] That's
the <i>Larchmont Charter.</i>

49:12.382 --> 49:15.215
It's the best. You gotta read
your local paper, Ivan.

49:15.217 --> 49:18.519
North of the crease,
east of the fold.

49:18.521 --> 49:21.421
A 40-year-old fella found dead
in the L.A. River.

49:21.423 --> 49:24.657
No history of drugs. No priors.
Beaten, tortured.

49:24.659 --> 49:27.293
Shot in the head. No survivors.

49:27.295 --> 49:29.764
Skip to the last paragraph.
Went to Cal Arts.

49:29.766 --> 49:31.201
Worked at the museums.

49:32.568 --> 49:33.570
Do you know him?

49:35.605 --> 49:37.137
No.

49:37.139 --> 49:40.106
- Never seen him before.
- [Ray] Huh.

49:40.108 --> 49:43.510
Anyway, uh, I gotta finish this
and then get back to work.

49:43.512 --> 49:45.278
You gotta punch the clock, huh?

49:45.280 --> 49:47.048
[Ivan] Yup.

49:47.050 --> 49:48.382
Back to the salt mines.

49:48.384 --> 49:49.784
Nose to the stones.
Is that right?

49:49.786 --> 49:51.818
Exactly. What the fuck
are you asking me, Ray?

49:51.820 --> 49:53.356
I don't know, man. I don't know.

49:54.590 --> 49:56.157
I don't know.

49:56.159 --> 49:58.224
I mean, I haven't been around,
but this seems to me

49:58.226 --> 50:01.162
like maybe you're trying
to clean up one of Dad's messes.

50:01.164 --> 50:03.266
Yeah? Well, I think
that's the way it works.

50:04.400 --> 50:05.568
Got it. Well...
[slurps]

50:07.070 --> 50:08.501
...read your local paper.

50:08.503 --> 50:10.072
Keep your head on a swivel.

50:11.740 --> 50:13.773
And here.

50:13.775 --> 50:16.077
- Look what I dug up.
- What the fuck is that?

50:16.079 --> 50:17.744
Dad's gun.

50:17.746 --> 50:19.280
Why the fuck
have you got Dad's gun?

50:19.282 --> 50:20.347
I don't want that.

50:20.349 --> 50:21.514
Well, now, see,

50:21.516 --> 50:22.583
I do, but I don't think

50:22.585 --> 50:24.452
I'm the one
that really needs it.

50:24.454 --> 50:26.220
[Ray] You know how to use that?

50:26.222 --> 50:28.322
Manual's in the box.

50:28.324 --> 50:30.159
How's your German?
Mine's a bit rusty.

50:32.461 --> 50:33.630
[Ray grunts]

50:34.496 --> 50:35.531
[gun clicks]

50:37.632 --> 50:39.135
I think it goes the other way.

50:41.304 --> 50:43.369
[Ray] Oh, by the way,
there's a fella in a Crown Vic

50:43.371 --> 50:45.438
on the corner there.

50:45.440 --> 50:46.675
He's been there all morning.

50:48.344 --> 50:49.409
Probably nothin'.

50:49.411 --> 50:50.579
[gun clicking]

51:02.891 --> 51:05.094
[machine chiming]

51:05.661 --> 51:07.364
[beeping]

51:10.666 --> 51:12.501
[whirring]

51:13.735 --> 51:14.737
[beeps]

51:18.875 --> 51:21.641
[foreboding music]

51:21.643 --> 51:24.146
[indistinct chatter]

51:25.313 --> 51:26.880
- [dealer] Big blind?
- Sure.

51:26.882 --> 51:28.414
How much behind?

51:28.416 --> 51:30.286
- [Elyse] 500.
- [dealer] Chips, 500.

51:32.221 --> 51:33.222
Thank you.

51:34.590 --> 51:36.093
Continue, five.

51:36.659 --> 51:37.760
To your right.

51:44.599 --> 51:45.601
Call.

51:48.403 --> 51:50.938
Uh, raise. Make it 110.

51:50.940 --> 51:52.639
- [dealer] Raise 100?
- [Elyse] All in.

51:52.641 --> 51:53.876
[dealer] The lady is all in.

51:54.777 --> 51:55.943
[player] I'll fold.

51:55.945 --> 51:57.478
[dealer] Looks like
it's up to you, sir.

51:57.480 --> 51:58.912
I'm laying the deal.

51:58.914 --> 52:00.117
He calls.

52:04.554 --> 52:05.588
[Elyse] Run 'em.

52:12.460 --> 52:13.562
[dealer] Good luck, everybody.

52:17.867 --> 52:19.269
[dealer] Set of kings wins.

52:20.503 --> 52:21.505
Sorry.

52:22.371 --> 52:23.606
Can I get one of those?

52:26.742 --> 52:27.911
Good luck. Bad beat.

52:32.748 --> 52:34.550
[crowd cheering]

52:37.452 --> 52:38.721
[man laughing]

52:39.688 --> 52:42.224
[indistinct chatter]

52:42.925 --> 52:44.928
[crowd cheering]

52:50.900 --> 52:53.800
That's what I'm talkin' about.
That's what I'm talkin' about.

52:53.802 --> 52:56.570
Hey, little lady.
You watchin' or you playin'?

52:56.572 --> 52:58.706
Well, I don't know.
What should I do?

52:58.708 --> 52:59.874
I think you oughta play.

52:59.876 --> 53:00.941
Why don't you come over here
and let Big Daddy show you

53:00.943 --> 53:01.842
- how to do this, all right?
- [Elyse] All right.

53:01.844 --> 53:05.746
- Now, you blow on them dice.
- Oh, okay.

53:05.748 --> 53:06.847
- That's it. All right.
- Uh-huh.

53:06.849 --> 53:08.282
Gimme a yo, Adrian.

53:08.284 --> 53:10.416
Here we go. Comin' out now.
Comin' out.

53:10.418 --> 53:11.284
[crowd cheering]

53:11.286 --> 53:12.619
Yeah, that's what
I'm talking about!

53:12.621 --> 53:14.255
No, whoa, whoa, where you going?

53:14.257 --> 53:15.688
- You're my good luck.
- Oh.

53:15.690 --> 53:17.258
You don't need good luck.

53:17.260 --> 53:19.260
You know I don't.
Gimme a drink over here.

53:19.262 --> 53:20.228
Come on now.

53:20.230 --> 53:22.465
All right. Comin' out again.
Hot potatoes!

53:23.699 --> 53:24.967
- Hey, Janice.
- Hey.

53:25.900 --> 53:27.536
I'd use the north exit.

53:28.403 --> 53:29.336
Really?

53:29.338 --> 53:31.871
Yeah. The front's crawling
with security.

53:31.873 --> 53:33.309
All right. Thank you.

53:33.809 --> 53:35.342
How are you?

53:35.344 --> 53:36.876
Every day
is better than the last.

53:36.878 --> 53:37.880
[Elyse] Hmm.

53:40.782 --> 53:43.650
[Elyse] <i>I feel
the exact same way.</i>

53:43.652 --> 53:44.751
[Janice] <i>All right, girl.
Good luck.</i>

53:44.753 --> 53:45.755
[Elyse] <i>You too.</i>

53:51.726 --> 53:53.730
[foreboding music]

53:59.302 --> 54:00.804
[keys jangling]

54:06.909 --> 54:08.508
Your money is in there.

54:08.510 --> 54:10.579
That parking's
reserved for executives.

54:11.347 --> 54:12.449
They'll tell you.

54:13.648 --> 54:14.981
Great dress.

54:14.983 --> 54:16.816
Bet it looked better last night.

54:16.818 --> 54:18.052
[scoffs]

54:18.054 --> 54:19.353
[car alarm beeps]

54:19.355 --> 54:20.523
[Aton] Yo, you got 'em?

54:21.090 --> 54:23.460
[clanking]

54:24.893 --> 54:26.895
[foreboding music]

54:30.800 --> 54:32.602
[car engine starts]

54:37.373 --> 54:38.474
[Ivan] Gentlemen.

54:39.007 --> 54:40.641
How'd it go?

54:40.643 --> 54:42.976
Well, I'm alive.

54:42.978 --> 54:45.612
So, where is Hitler? You're
walking with both arms swinging.

54:45.614 --> 54:47.981
Yeah. That's, uh...

54:47.983 --> 54:49.717
That's what I wanted to
talk to you about.

54:49.719 --> 54:50.987
I don't like the sound of this.

54:52.355 --> 54:54.621
There was a... complication.

54:54.623 --> 54:55.688
What are you talking about?

54:55.690 --> 54:57.891
[sighs, clicks tongue]

54:57.893 --> 54:59.892
I'm talking about the FBI.
They're on to me.

54:59.894 --> 55:01.695
One agent in particular.

55:01.697 --> 55:04.831
No! No, no, no! Goddamn it, no!

55:04.833 --> 55:06.368
[Dimitri]
This is not the way this goes.

55:07.469 --> 55:08.336
Did you talk to this guy?

55:08.338 --> 55:09.302
No, of course,
I didn't talk to him.

55:09.304 --> 55:11.637
So, how do you know for sure
that he's FBI?

55:11.639 --> 55:13.539
Because he has
a government license plate,

55:13.541 --> 55:15.708
and he doesn't exactly look
like a census worker.

55:15.710 --> 55:16.779
[Dimitri] Jesus!

55:18.447 --> 55:19.248
[cocks gun]

55:20.815 --> 55:23.583
Jesus fucking Christ.
What is this?

55:23.585 --> 55:25.084
This is me.

55:25.086 --> 55:26.987
And I am telling you

55:26.989 --> 55:31.157
that you are gonna come clean,
100%, right fucking now.

55:31.159 --> 55:32.159
[Ivan] Okay.

55:32.161 --> 55:36.162
I didn't talk to him.
I would never do that.

55:36.164 --> 55:37.798
Why are you pointing
a gun in my face?

55:37.800 --> 55:40.601
You are making me
point this gun in your face.

55:40.603 --> 55:42.338
Aren't you forgetting something,
Dimitri?

55:43.639 --> 55:45.505
- Where is Hitler?
- I have him.

55:45.507 --> 55:46.875
Why didn't you bring him?
Why isn't he here?

55:47.742 --> 55:48.744
For insurance.

55:51.914 --> 55:54.180
You do realize you're kind of
out of your depth here, right?

55:54.182 --> 55:56.450
Yeah, I'm becoming
more aware of that.

55:56.452 --> 55:58.017
Listen to me.
[chuckles]

55:58.019 --> 55:59.887
There was never gonna be
any kind of shooting at all.

55:59.889 --> 56:02.923
This was me, testing you.

56:02.925 --> 56:05.691
- Believe me, it's all fine.
- [Ivan] Okay.

56:05.693 --> 56:06.730
It's fine.

56:09.465 --> 56:12.465
It... It's...
It's for the splatter.

56:12.467 --> 56:14.168
There was never gonna be
any fucking splatter.

56:14.170 --> 56:16.068
Okay, I'm getting outta here.

56:16.070 --> 56:17.139
Wait! Wait!

56:20.842 --> 56:22.508
What is this?

56:22.510 --> 56:24.043
[Dimitri]
That is your last hurrah.

56:24.045 --> 56:25.746
I've made you
a shitload of money.

56:25.748 --> 56:26.813
I'm letting you out
the back door,

56:26.815 --> 56:28.449
which is something I do not do.

56:28.451 --> 56:30.050
[Dimitri] Get me that sculpture
that's being fenced

56:30.052 --> 56:31.084
in that safe house.

56:31.086 --> 56:34.887
You bring me Hitler,
and that's it. That's it.

56:34.889 --> 56:36.956
[Dimitri] We call it a day.

56:36.958 --> 56:39.461
It's <i>The Nose by Giacometti.</i>
You know it?

56:41.530 --> 56:42.896
Never heard of it. No.

56:42.898 --> 56:44.401
[Dimitri] Well, it's a big deal.

56:44.800 --> 56:45.802
Great.

56:48.903 --> 56:49.905
[Dimitri] Ivan.

56:52.942 --> 56:53.943
Take care.

57:03.518 --> 57:05.521
[foreboding music]

57:24.739 --> 57:26.542
[car engine revs]

57:51.699 --> 57:52.768
[Ivan] Hey, man.

57:59.074 --> 58:00.476
How's the hash?

58:02.911 --> 58:04.811
That shit was good.

58:04.813 --> 58:06.749
But you should know.
It's your joint.

58:08.083 --> 58:09.586
Seems like you wanna talk.

58:11.019 --> 58:14.220
I didn't think you'd spot me
with this disguise.

58:14.222 --> 58:15.956
[clears throat]

58:15.958 --> 58:18.126
Lyman Wilkers, FBI.

58:20.195 --> 58:23.095
No need to introduce yourself,
Mr. Warding.

58:23.097 --> 58:25.599
- I've taken the liberty.
- [Ivan] Mm-hm.

58:25.601 --> 58:27.034
Why are you following me?

58:27.036 --> 58:29.101
I'm not following you.

58:29.103 --> 58:31.637
I'm watching you.
There's a big difference.

58:31.639 --> 58:34.874
If I was following you,
I'd need taps, surveillance,

58:34.876 --> 58:36.208
signatures from judges.

58:36.210 --> 58:38.811
Well, it kinda seems like
you're following me.

58:38.813 --> 58:40.847
- I'll have a coffee.
- [waitress] You got it.

58:40.849 --> 58:42.215
Look, you're better at this
than me,

58:42.217 --> 58:43.853
so I'll just come clean.

58:45.054 --> 58:46.987
You mind if I come clean?

58:46.989 --> 58:47.990
[Ivan] Please do.

58:50.626 --> 58:51.961
It's not hard to find you.

58:53.929 --> 58:56.662
You get ten dipshits
on the Internet,

58:56.664 --> 58:59.032
and you can find the 50
or 60 guys

58:59.034 --> 59:01.070
who install art
for a living around here.

59:02.605 --> 59:04.338
[Lyman] Let's see here.

59:04.340 --> 59:07.173
Worked for
two private install firms, uh,

59:07.175 --> 59:09.778
Cooper-Beasley
and Montrose Partners,

59:11.112 --> 59:14.081
a couple of museums
after art school.

59:14.083 --> 59:15.849
And you wanna know the truth?

59:15.851 --> 59:18.251
It was an eyewitness.

59:18.253 --> 59:20.222
There is nothin'
like an eyewitness.

59:21.056 --> 59:22.659
Even if it's just a kid.

59:23.759 --> 59:24.860
[rustles]

59:28.831 --> 59:32.132
[Lyman] It's not a bad likeness,
if you ask me.

59:32.134 --> 59:35.401
They got a little fat
in the cheeks, but, uh,

59:35.403 --> 59:37.371
I think that's
the sketch artist's fault.

59:37.373 --> 59:38.639
Not hers.

59:38.641 --> 59:40.641
Yeah, probably.

59:40.643 --> 59:43.776
- What are you asking me?
- [Lyman sighs]

59:43.778 --> 59:47.347
I've been a field agent
for 17 years, and...

59:47.349 --> 59:50.916
I've hit what they call
the black ceiling.

59:50.918 --> 59:53.787
I think it's time for a change.
Maybe...

59:53.789 --> 59:57.891
something inside
with a less municipal car,

59:57.893 --> 59:59.695
and, um...
[soft grunt]

01:00:00.695 --> 01:00:03.130
Fuck it, I'm just gonna say it.

01:00:03.132 --> 01:00:07.333
No more petty shakedowns
with shitheaps like yourself.

01:00:07.335 --> 01:00:10.003
In the past three years, you
and your pals have taken down

01:00:10.005 --> 01:00:12.104
over $75 million

01:00:12.106 --> 01:00:14.441
- in gray market art.
- [Ivan clears throat]

01:00:14.443 --> 01:00:16.108
Here's the thing.

01:00:16.110 --> 01:00:17.744
I don't care
if you think you got this

01:00:17.746 --> 01:00:19.012
tighter than a nun's cunt,

01:00:19.014 --> 01:00:21.180
- you gonna slip up.
- [Ivan] Mm-hm.

01:00:21.182 --> 01:00:23.983
It might not be you.
It might be a...

01:00:23.985 --> 01:00:26.452
unstable girlfriend,

01:00:26.454 --> 01:00:30.257
or a bipolar brother.

01:00:30.259 --> 01:00:32.958
But there's always a crack.

01:00:32.960 --> 01:00:35.262
[Lyman] Did I mention I've been
doin' this for 17 years?

01:00:35.264 --> 01:00:37.030
Yeah. You did.

01:00:37.032 --> 01:00:39.298
That's twice,
and as far as I can tell,

01:00:39.300 --> 01:00:40.900
you have my resumé

01:00:40.902 --> 01:00:43.138
and the testimony
of a four-year-old girl.

01:00:45.074 --> 01:00:46.175
Oh, Ivan.

01:00:50.311 --> 01:00:53.016
I don't seem to remember
telling you she was four.

01:00:54.416 --> 01:00:56.318
[Lyman] Just a good guess,
I suppose.

01:00:57.052 --> 01:00:58.320
[chuckles]

01:01:04.092 --> 01:01:05.391
What do you want from me?

01:01:05.393 --> 01:01:07.195
[Lyman] Let's get
one thing straight.

01:01:08.030 --> 01:01:09.929
You're useless.

01:01:09.931 --> 01:01:11.063
I don't care about you.

01:01:11.065 --> 01:01:12.331
You mean nothin' to me.

01:01:12.333 --> 01:01:14.200
Unless...

01:01:14.202 --> 01:01:16.338
and that's with a capital U,

01:01:17.840 --> 01:01:20.108
you can deliver me
the man with the plan.

01:01:21.210 --> 01:01:23.175
'Cause if not,

01:01:23.177 --> 01:01:25.981
it's gonna be my foot
in your ass.

01:01:27.849 --> 01:01:29.251
Hmmm.
[sighs]

01:01:39.094 --> 01:01:40.797
You still got a fax machine?

01:01:41.963 --> 01:01:43.099
Fuck you.

01:01:49.771 --> 01:01:50.907
[door slams]

01:01:54.208 --> 01:01:55.411
[cracks]

01:01:59.981 --> 01:02:02.150
[tense music]

01:02:11.960 --> 01:02:13.963
[suspenseful music]

01:02:20.302 --> 01:02:22.369
[Melanie] <i>Well, like I said,
great kitchen.</i>

01:02:22.371 --> 01:02:24.804
<i>Great for cooking meals.</i>

01:02:24.806 --> 01:02:26.539
<i>And the house, I mean,</i>

01:02:26.541 --> 01:02:28.874
<i>unlike a lot of the homes
in Costa Mesa,</i>

01:02:28.876 --> 01:02:30.811
- hasn't been touched in years.
- Mm.

01:02:30.813 --> 01:02:32.412
So, a lot of potential.

01:02:32.414 --> 01:02:34.246
I see it. It's beautiful.

01:02:34.248 --> 01:02:35.315
Ooh.

01:02:35.317 --> 01:02:36.449
We lost your boyfriend.

01:02:36.451 --> 01:02:38.385
Um, he'll resurface.
He always does.

01:02:38.387 --> 01:02:40.487
- Oh, okay.
- I love your shoes, by the way.

01:02:40.489 --> 01:02:42.454
- Oh, my god, thank you.
- They're beautiful.

01:02:42.456 --> 01:02:43.889
Nordstrom Rack.

01:02:43.891 --> 01:02:45.057
- No.
- Yes!

01:02:45.059 --> 01:02:47.126
- [scoffs]
- [Melanie chuckles]

01:02:47.128 --> 01:02:49.963
So, anyway, real opportunity
to do something special here.

01:02:49.965 --> 01:02:51.463
[Elyse] Mm-hm.

01:02:51.465 --> 01:02:53.599
My boyfriend is impossible.
I don't know where he is.

01:02:53.601 --> 01:02:54.867
- I'm so sorry.
- I heard that.

01:02:54.869 --> 01:02:56.836
- Oh, hello.
- Hey.

01:02:56.838 --> 01:02:59.539
Well, if it was up to me,
I'd be calling the movers,

01:02:59.541 --> 01:03:02.909
but you know men. He's gonna hem
and haw for two and three weeks.

01:03:02.911 --> 01:03:03.976
[chuckles]
Right?

01:03:03.978 --> 01:03:05.045
- It's true.
- Yeah.

01:03:05.047 --> 01:03:07.213
- Thank you so much, Melanie.
- Oh.

01:03:07.215 --> 01:03:08.347
- Thank you, Candace.
- [Elyse chuckles]

01:03:08.349 --> 01:03:09.548
Great to meet you. Thank you.

01:03:09.550 --> 01:03:11.617
- It was a pleasure, Terry.
- Uh-huh.

01:03:11.619 --> 01:03:13.221
You're such a cute couple.

01:03:14.956 --> 01:03:16.021
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

01:03:16.023 --> 01:03:17.090
All right. Have a good day.

01:03:17.092 --> 01:03:17.923
- Thanks. Take care.
- [Elyse] We'll be in touch.

01:03:17.925 --> 01:03:19.394
- [Ivan] Bye-bye.
- [Melanie] Bye-bye.

01:03:23.097 --> 01:03:24.296
[Elyse] <i>Did you find anything?</i>

01:03:24.298 --> 01:03:25.599
Well, I'm definitely
getting set up.

01:03:25.601 --> 01:03:26.900
Is that good?

